@node Introduction "Introduction"
@NEXT Requirements
@PREV Main
@WORDWRAP

@{B}Introduction:@{UB}

@{B}SCANdal @{UB}is a graphic interface for scanner drivers in @{B}Betascan/SANE@{UB} standard. It uses MUI and was ported on all Amiga-like operating systems (MorphOS, AmigaOS 4.x, AmigaOS3.x, AROS). The point of its developing was to provide their users a free software that allows them to use scanners effectively and uses advanced functions of new version of the mentioned operating systems.
@ENDNODE

@node Requirements "Requirements"
@NEXT Installation
@PREV Introduction
@WORDWRAP

@{B}Requirements@{UB}:

For proper use of @{B}SCANdal@{UB} you need the following components to be installed in your system:
- MUI (Magic User Interface) version 3.8 or later
- urltext.mcc MUI class

For MorphOS version lower than 2.x
- Update Pack containing @{B}jfif.library@{UB} and @{B}png.library@{UB} as well as an @{B}Aboutbox.mcc@{UB} class
- MorphOS version of this software uses advanced MUI 4.x, so it may not work properly with older MUI versions

Additionally the computer should be fitted with a proper hardware interface (SCSI or USB) to connect your scanner to. You should also have proper scanner drivers for @{B}Betascan@{UB} standard installed. SCANdal as a graphic interface does not give the possibility to scan anything without proper drivers available.
@ENDNODE

@node Installation "Installation"
@PREV Requirements
@WORDWRAP

@{B}Installation@{UB}:

SCANdal is ready to run right after decompressing the archive in destination directory and doesn't copy any files into any other directories. For proper working it requires Betascan drivers in #?.device form to be present in any directory on you hard drive.

@ENDNODE

@node FAQ "Frequently Asked Questions"
@WORDWRAP

@{B} Frequently Asked Questions@{UB}:

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Will SCANdal work with my XXX scanner?
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  SCANdal as a graphic interface supports scanner that have Betascan drivers available. Betascan drivers are based on SANE standard. SANE drivers that are possible to port are listed here: 
@{B}http://www.sane-project.org/sane-mfgs.html@{UB}
However the fact that any SANE driver exists doesn't imply easy Betascan driver creation process.

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Are all functions of my scanner (such as AFD or advanced preferences) supported by SCANdal?
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  For now, only those scanner functions, that SCANdal is tested with are supported. Additional options will be added in incoming versions. 

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Why there is no AROS version available?
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  AROS version exists, and the code has AROS support implemented. It will be released after finishing the drivers’ development, together with their AROS version.  

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Can I support SCANdal development anyhow?
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  I would really appreciate the following support:
  - testing SCANdal on different hardware/software configurations, and sending debug logs if any element isn’t working properly
  - translating locale to any yet unsupported language
  - hardware support: if you have any scanner that is unnecessary or not used anymore (it can even be old), and you are willing to give it to the author, it would be really helpful in further development and testing

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Does SCANdal work with USB scanners?  
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  It should work with any scanner that has Betascan driver available. There have been some problems with EpsonUSB.device reported. They will be eliminated as soon, as I get my hands on any supported Epson scanner.

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Will future Betascan drivers be different from 68k version?
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  Yes, 68k Betascan version was created with SAS C compiler with inlined assembler code. It also used unixlib library for SAS C, which is a compilation of posix functions with implemented things, such as: streams, file access via descriptors, fork() functions etc. Betascan version for new systems is base only on standard system functions, so for some of the drivers the amount of work during porting is greater than in others. What’s more, USB support will be realized without using #?.device needed to communicate with the hardware.

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Will there be any new save formats?  
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  Yes. Additionally in MorphOS system, saving images will be based on Reggae system.

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Will there be any version for computers without graphic card?  
@{B}Answer: @{UB}
  Adding 8 bit screens support is being taken into consideration, but has a low priority.  

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  I would like to ask about?
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  Send it to author via email.  

@{B}Question:@{UB}
  Should Hyperion Entertainment port AmigaOS4 to PlayStation3?
@{B}Answer:@{UB}
  Yes, of course. Digging in broken glass with rubber-made glasses is very helpful in intellectual development of mouse pointer.
@ENDNODE

@node History "History"
@WORDWRAP

@{B}History@{UB}:

(1.0)
 - first working version for MorphOS
 - scanning support
 - changing scanning modes (RGB, LineArt, Grey)
 - changing scanning resolution
 - saving in PNG, JPEG, IFF DEEP

(1.1)
 - localizations
 - Gamma correction, changing: brightness, negative modes
 - auto adding of file extension
 - added file overwrite requester
 - first release for AmigaOS 3.x and AmigaOs 4.x
 - AROS version preparations
 - MUIScan name changed to SCANdal 
 - bugtracker added: http://www.ppa.pl/bugtracker/index.php?id=6

(1.2)
 - scanning in preview mode added
 - printing with Turboprint drivers added
 - added scanner information tab 
 - "Scan and save" button has been activated
 - Polish documentation has been added
 - minor fixes for MorphOS 1.4.5 
 - added possibility to resize existing scan area frame
 - in case of lack of memory proper error window is displayed 
 - EpsonUSB and Mustek scanners communication has been improved

(1.3)
 - Autocrop (works best with LineArt mode)
 - Autoconnect tooltype, Connect button
 - saving in PDF, TIFF
 - Fixed JPEG saver
 - Sketch plugin support
 - Fixed Mode list and DPI Radio (for gt68xx driver)


